  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you cook cube steak?",
  "response": "Cooking cube steak is relatively straightforward, and there are several methods you can use depending on your preference. Here\u2019s a guide to help you prepare it:\n\n### 1. **Seasoning the Steak**\n   - Start by seasoning the cube steak with salt and pepper on both sides. You can also use additional seasonings like garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, or your favorite steak seasoning blend.\n\n### 2. **Pan-Frying Cube Steak**\n   - **Heat the Pan:** Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add a couple of tablespoons of oil (vegetable, canola, or olive oil work well).\n   - **Dredge in Flour (Optional):** For a crispy coating, you can dredge the cube steaks in seasoned flour before frying.\n   - **Cook the Steak:** Place the cube steaks in the hot skillet. Cook for about 3-4 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. Avoid overcrowding the pan to ensure even browning.\n   - **Rest:** Remove the steaks from the pan and let them rest for a few minutes before serving.\n\n### 3. **Making Gravy (Optional)**\n   - After cooking the steaks, you can use the pan drippings to make a simple gravy.\n   - **Deglaze the Pan:** Leave about 2 tablespoons of drippings in the pan and add 2 tablespoons of flour. Stir to combine and cook for 1-2 minutes.\n   - **Add Liquid:** Gradually whisk in 1-2 cups of beef broth or milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Bring to a simmer and cook until the gravy thickens.\n   - **Season:** Taste and add salt, pepper, or other seasonings as needed.\n\n### 4. **Baking or Braising Cube Steak**\n   - **Preheat the Oven:** Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).\n   - **Sear the Steak:** Sear the cube steaks in a skillet as described above, then transfer them to a baking dish.\n   - **Add Liquid:** Pour a cup of beef broth, cream of mushroom soup, or your preferred sauce over the steaks.\n   - **Cover and Bake:** Cover the dish with foil and bake for about 1-1.5 hours, or until the meat is tender.\n\n### 5. **Slow Cooking Cube Steak**\n   - **Prepare the Steak:** Season the cube steaks and sear them in a skillet if desired.\n   - **Add Ingredients:** Place the steaks in a slow cooker and add ingredients like onions, mushrooms, or a can of cream of mushroom soup.\n   - **Cook:** Cook on low for 6-8 hours or on high for 3-4 hours, until the meat is tender.\n\n### Serving Suggestions\n   - Serve cube steak with mashed potatoes, steamed vegetables, or rice. If you made gravy, pour it over the steak and sides.\n\n### Tips\n   - Cube steak is tenderized, so it\u2019s best cooked quickly or braised/slow-cooked for a soft, melt-in-your-mouth texture.\n   - Be careful not to overcook cube steak, as it can become tough.\n\nEnjoy your cube steak meal!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
